post_text:
Hello UNC Warriors,

This message pertains to all UNC Warrior Cross Country runners and any students 7th-12th grade interested in joining Cross Country. Cross Country practice will begin on Monday, August 17th. Practice will be from 7am-9am. Monday-Thursday practices will be at the track in Sebeka and Friday's will be in Menahga.

Menahga athletes will load the bus in front of the District office doors. The bus will leave from the District doors at 6:45am to head down to Sebeka. Please be on the bus 5-10 minutes early as we will have to do health checks. Cross Country is an outdoor sport and no mask will be required to wear when outside and/or during practice, but a mask will be needed when riding the bus and/or if we have to go inside.

We are very happy that the CC season is a go! We know it may look different with everything that is going on, but if we all work together we can make this yet again another successful Warriors Cross Country season!

Coach Jasmer
Coach Oyster
Coach Smith

post_text:
Greetings, Menahga Families! I hope this message finds you all well, and enjoying what is left of this beautiful, MN summer!! I want to assure you we are working on planning, while also following the guidance from the state. Families and staff will receive a survey soon, to help us with this continued planning. Thank you so much for your patience and understanding. Our number one priority continues to be the education and safety of our kids and staff that attend the Menahga School District. Thank you so much for all you do!!

If you still have devices from last spring, please return them to the district office, clearly labeled with your student's name and grade from last year. We would like to ensure our devices are updated.

Also, just a reminder of that Menahga Public School will be providing all school supplies for the school year, with the exception of a pencil box, headphones, and a backpack.

post_text:
Greetings All!

The administrative team has made the decision to provide everything on the previous supply lists K-12 except things that are not consumable for all students for the coming school year. Backpacks, headphones, supply boxes, clothing/gym shoes as well as high school class specific items are the responsibility of the family. All other supplies including pencils, erasers, markers, scissors, binders, glue, notebooks, wipes, Kleenex etc...will be provided for every student to start the year.

This decision has been made so we can be consistent for all students and give families a break in these challenging times. Please adjust your back to school shopping accordingly.

As a side note, The Menahga School Board fully intends and will financially support the return of students and staff to school to start the 2020-2021 school year and will provide reasonable accommodations for those students and staff exhibiting symptoms of COVID-19 or have underlying conditions as defined by MDH and the CDC. We are planning accordingly.
--
Kevin Wellen, Superintendent
Menahga Schools

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5-18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals. The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit.
Learn more at: www.mn.p-ebt.org

Did your child participate in free or reduced-price school meals? Because schools are closed, a new program can help provide a food benefit. Take a moment to apply for P-EBT.
Apply today: www.mn.p-ebt.org

post_text: Menahga Elementary celebrates AmeriCorps Week – from the programs and organizations that make this national service initiative possible in communities across the country. One program under AmeriCorps is MN Reading Corps, which we have here at Menahga. We are thankful to have two members of the program, Kathy Wenner and Jim Ertl serving our students this year. They spend time each day tutoring students to improve their literacy with the overall goal of all students being proficient in reading by the end of 3rd grade.
text: Menahga Elementary celebrates AmeriCorps Week – from the programs and organizations that make this national service initiative possible in communities across the country. One program under AmeriCorps is MN Reading Corps, which we have here at Menahga. We are thankful to have two members of the program, Kathy Wenner and Jim Ertl serving our students this year. They spend time each day tutoring students to improve their literacy with the overall goal of all students being proficient in reading by the end of 3rd grade.

post_text: Mr. Hahn’s Adapted Physical Education students and Special Olympics athletes participated in the 40th Annual Winter Carnival at Camp Confidence in Brainard, MN. Events included everything from dog sled rides, snowmobile rides, snowshoeing, ice bowling, broom ball, tubing, and ice fishing, just to name a few. A huge thanks goes out to all the volunteer help of Menahga students and staff who helped make this a very memorable day for all of our Menahga Special Olympics athletes. It was fun-filled event had by all!

Menahga Public School added 6 new photos — in Menahga, Minnesota.
March 10 at 3:53 PM · Menahga, MN ·

Ms. Rossbach teaches a class called the Art of the Unique Technique where students learn some of the more high-end arts and crafts and sometimes kitsch art processes (think painting on velvet!). Years ago, Ms. Rossbach consulted Mr. Lonnie Schmidt on what materials and tools were needed to start this only as a reference to get her dad started on stained glass. A few years later, after he mastered the art form, he taught it to Ms. Rossbach, who now, in turn, teaches her students not only how to do stained glass but design the patterns for it. That in itself is a tricky one! You just never know where or when you're going to learn something new, but we do and when the stories come full circle....well we just like to give credit where credit is due. Thanks, Mr. Schmidt for getting us started and Mr. Rossbach and Matthew John for their knowledge and wonderful donations of glass and more glass and even more glass!

post_text: The Menahga Gateway Lions sponsored their annual 5M9 Lions Poster contest. The Menahga 6th grade students participated with wonderful and creative posters. Menahga Public School
January 16 at 1:00 PM ·

Menahga School District will be altering their morning bus drop-off, effective Monday, January 20th. Students in grades Preschool-4th grade will be dropped off at Elementary doors #1N & #2N. Middle School and High School students will be dropped off at the Middle and High School doors #7E, #8E and #10E. Please refrain from using the bus drop-off lanes between 7:50 and 8:10. This will allow the buses to get in and out of the parking lots, efficiently. If you are dropping students off, please park in the parking lot, and walk across the crosswalk, where there will be crossing guards. Cars are not allowed in the bus drop-off lane during loading and unloading times.
Thank you for your continued cooperation as we focus on the safety of all of our students.
Menahga School Administration

Menahga students enrolled in Ms. Rossbach's high school Drawing Class have begun their self-portraits. These larger-than-life artworks utilize the skill sets acquired from the beginning of September until now. The students posed and took the photos to reference, will use the grid method and choose to work with either graphite or charcoal to render their self-portrait. The process usually takes 5 to 6 weeks to complete which is approximately 30 hours of drawing!

post_text: A BIG TIME congratulations goes out to two outstanding Menahga Special Olympic athletes! Will Peterson and Henry Hultberg were recognized at the University of Minnesota Golden Gophers Hockey game on Saturday, November 23rd for their school spirit, positive attitude, and involvement and leadership within Menahga's Special Olympics sports program. For their recognition, both Will and Henry received free game tickets to the University of Minnesota Golden Gophers Hockey game where Affinity Plus presented them with "Special Olympic Athlete of the Game" recognition.

post_text: On Wednesday, September 25th, the Menahga Braves Special Olympics team participated in a Unified Flag Football event in Pillager, MN. For this event many of Mr. Hahn’s Adapted Physical Education students teamed-up with Menahga High School students to make a unified flag football team. The Menahga Braves ended up taking home first place ribbions and it was a great time had by all. A BIG thanks goes out to all the Menahga volunteers that helped make this day possible for Menahga's Special Olympics athletes.

post_text:
Students in Ms. Rossbach's Art 8 Class are creating "Art Shacks" which are based loosely on the works of Beverly Buchanan and address the theme of "Place and Identity." Students use the design process where they brainstorm ideas around what and how place affects their identity. Taking those ideas further they research artists and art styles along with techniques they might try, the sketch out their ideas for their final designs, documenting their process along the way.

Discussions about the words "feeling out of place" and "home is where the heart is" became two springboards to start generating ideas of how to express this theme while learning how to design and construct 3-D forms. Look for more photos as they finish up their work.

post_text: Mr. Hahn’s DAPE students had their last BIG event of the school year on Tuesday, May 28th -- DAPE FISHING-ADVENTURE DAY! This fun filled event took place on Fishhook lake and the Heartland Park in Park Rapids. Everything was provided for students including the rods, reels, bait, tackle, and lifejackets. This was a tremendous opportunity for these kids and a great day had by all. A big thanks to Mr. Schultz for providing another fishing boat and to all the Menahga Paraprofessionals and Menahga High School students who helped in making this day possible for our adaptive students. Also, a huge thanks to the Menahga Shell Gas Station for their donation of the live bait.

post_text: On Wednesday, May 8, the Menahga Braves Special Olympics team participated in a track and field event in Pillager, MN. For this event, many of Mr. Hahn’s Adapted Physical Education students teamed-up with Menahga High School athletes to make unified relay teams. The Menahga Special Olympic athletes also participated in other running events like the 50-meter dash, the 200-meter run, the 400-meter run, and also field events like the shot put and softball toss. Huge thanks go out to all the volunteer help of the Menahga High School students who helped make this a very memorable day for Mr. Hahn’s Adapted Physical Education students! It was a great day had by all!

Menahga Public School added 15 new photos.
April 24, 2019 at 8:24 PM ·

Four Menahga High School students competed in the 2019 MSHSL Regional Visual Arts Festival held in New York Mills on April 24. Attending were Taryn Laulainen, Sam Juntunen, Anna Besonen, and Sufa Shahin. In order to participate, students must be in good standing academically, write an artist statement and submit an artwork according to the MSHSL rules and regulations. Menahga students submitted seven artworks and took home 6 awards!

Taking home ratings of Excellent for their artworks (16-17 points out of 20) were Sufa Shahin, Anna Besonen, and Sam Juntunen!

Taking home ratings of Superior (18-20 points out of 20) were Sufa Shahin and Anna Besonen!

Taking home the Best of Category in the Painting was Anna Besonen for her painting titled Ophelia!

Congratulations to the artists!

post_text: Second Graders spent Monday and Tuesday working with "Mrs. M." from Tech Mobile to learn, design and build! Students spent time in several centers using hands-on techniques and strategies to build structures from scratch. Students in Mrs. Koch's class took what they learned from Tech Mobile and transferred it to designing and building a contraption that would move "Sparkles" the snake from one side of the room to the other without the use of hands or touching the floor! All the groups in 2K were successful!
